;; Canonical cljfmt configuration for the c3kit-jig monorepo.
;;
;; This file is the single source of truth. It is symlinked into:
;;   - templates/<id>/cljfmt.edn   — each template; the CLI's fs/copy-tree
;;                                    follows the symlink during fetch so the
;;                                    scaffolded project ships a real file.
;;   - verification/cljfmt.edn     — the harness itself uses these rules on
;;                                    its own clj sources.
;;
;; The scaffolder runs cljfmt with this config as the final render step —
;; against the stripped output, not the marker-laden template — so cljfmt's
;; full ruleset is safe and the scaffold is born formatted. The verification
;; harness then runs `cljfmt check src spec dev` against the same files with
;; the same config, which is a no-op verification.
;;
;; Future templates: symlink their cljfmt.edn to this file. Don't fork.
;;
;; :extra-indents register block-style indentation so cljfmt does not align
;; bodies under the first argument (which would fight the 2-space body
;; indentation used throughout).
;;
;; Speclj test macros (describe/context/it/etc.) indent their bodies like
;; defn. c3kit.apron.corec/for-all is a comprehension macro shaped like for.
;; reagent.core/with-let is a binding macro shaped like let. Both bare and
;; fully-qualified forms are registered so the rule fires regardless of how
;; the caller aliases the namespace.
{:extra-indents
 {describe                  [[:block 1]]
  context                   [[:block 1]]
  it                        [[:block 1]]
  xit                       [[:block 1]]
  before                    [[:block 0]]
  before-all                [[:block 0]]
  after                     [[:block 0]]
  after-all                 [[:block 0]]
  around                    [[:block 1]]
  with                      [[:block 1]]
  with-all                  [[:block 1]]
  redefs-around             [[:block 1]]
  it-routes                 [[:block 2]]
  for-all                   [[:block 1]]
  c3kit.apron.corec/for-all [[:block 1]]
  with-let                  [[:block 1]]
  reagent.core/with-let     [[:block 1]]}}
